Modules

1. Each "button" listed in the Command Center corresponds to a "Module" in EMu.

Think of modules as separate databases where types of information are stored.

2. Click the "Catalog" button to open the "Catalog" module
3. A "Loading Module..." window will pop up, indicating that the module is being loaded
4. All modules look roughly the same

When you first open a module, it is shown as the "Search" view.

5. There are two toolbars at the top, followed by groupings of fields.

Feel free to click on each option at the toolbars to see what they do.


Each field has a label on the left and a textbox on the right, where you can type search parameters.

6. After the fields, you can see all the tabs that are available to you.

The arrow indicates the current tab that we are on.

7. Look at the bottom of a module to get information about your login

You can see your user name and what role (Group) you are logged in as at the bottom right of the module window.

8. The most commonly used modules accross collections are Catalog, Parties, Localities, Locations and Multimedia
9. Modules contain groups of information

However, modules may be inter connected. You can infer relationships between modules by looking at the fields.

For example, if you check the "Locality" field in the Catalog module, you will see that it has two icons to the right of it (highlighted here in pink rectangles). Those icons indicate that this field is an "attachment", that is, it is a piece of information that is related to the Catalog module, but that is being stored in a different module.
